                <h2>Cat Care</h2>
                <h3>Basic Care</h3>
                <p>Provide your cat with plenty of fresh water and nutritious food. Ensure your cat has a clean litter box and a comfortable place to rest.</p>
                
                <h3>Grooming</h3>
                <p>Regular grooming is important to keep your cat's coat healthy and to reduce shedding. Brush your cat's fur regularly and trim their nails as needed.</p>                
                <h3>Health</h3>
                <p>Regular veterinary check-ups are essential for maintaining your cat's health. Keep up with vaccinations, flea control, and any necessary treatments.</p>
                
                <h3>Exercise and Play</h3>
                <p>Cats need regular exercise and mental stimulation. Provide your cat with toys, climbing trees, and interactive play sessions.</p>
                
                <h3>Affection and Socialization</h3>
                <p>Spend time with your cat and show them affection. Proper socialization is important for their emotional well-being.</p>
                
